 From:  "vamsi@outplayhq.co" <vamsi@outplayhq.co>

 To:  Enrico Sulis <enrico.sulis@apicasystems.com> 
 Subject:  Re: Regarding your Reply.io review on G2 Crowd 
 
 
   
 
 
 Enrico,

cleaned_msg:
Hi David, 
 
 We use the Enhanced Email feature in Salesforce (Image 1 below). This is in tandem with the Salesforce plugin for Outlook. If they are sending emails through Outplay, does it know we use Enhanced Email? In other words, will both an EmailMessage
 record  and  completed Task be created or just a completed Task? 
 
 I ask because Enhanced Email gives us an API and a number of essential features we don’t get by using the outdated solution of logging completed Tasks for sent emails. 
 
 Aside from the ones mentioned in the image, these features include: 
 
 The date and time (not just date) that the email was sent, allowing the Activity Timeline to order the EmailMessage records (see Image 2 below). Tasks show out-of-order, making it
 difficult to track the chain of events. The sender and recipient are visible on the Activity Timeline. Also, the sender is not reliant on being the Task Owner, so changing the owner does not obscure the sender. Engagement metrics, such as when the email was opened and how many time is was viewed. I understand this is available in Outplay, but we should have this data in Salesforce too (as
 we currently do). Tasks are editable but EmailMessage records are not, thereby preserving the content and metadata of the email as it was originally sent. 
 
 Not to mention the API which allows us to hit the EmailMessage object and pull up emails in Salesforce using SOQL queries. 
 
 Image 1: 
 
 
 
 
 
 Image 2: 
 
 
 
 Best regards, 
 
 Ermin Bibic | Salesforce Administrator 
 ISSUER DIRECT CORPORATION | ACCESSWIRE 
 919.481.4000 ex: 503 
 issuerdirect.com  |  accesswire.com
